Sentencas: Exploring advanced electrode materials with high electrochemical performance and suf-ficient durability is crucial to the commercialization of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Boosting electrocatalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper type Fe-based cathode catalysts by La and Ni co-doping for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a Ruddlesden-Popper Sr2.9La0.1Fe1.9Ni0.1O7_(d) (SLFN) oxide is systematically evalu-ated as efficient oxygen electrode material.
Titulo: Boosting electrocatalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper type Fe-based cathode catalysts by La and Ni co-doping for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: La and Ni co-doping strategy demonstrates improved oxygen desorption ability and promoted electrochemical activity of pristine Sr3Fe2O7_d (SF) toward oxygen reduction react (ORR).
Titulo: Boosting electrocatalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper type Fe-based cathode catalysts by La and Ni co-doping for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Further, the ORR process of the SLFN electrode is probed by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) and distribution of relaxation time (DRT) technique.
Titulo: Boosting electrocatalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper type Fe-based cathode catalysts by La and Ni co-doping for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The button cell with the SLFN cathode delivers a peak power density of 1.01 W cm(_2 )at 700 ?, along with desirable stability over a period of 60 h. This study offers a feasible strategy for developing Ruddlesden-Popper type cathode can-didates for SOFCs.(C) 2022 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
